        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18618",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steve918",
                        "name": "steve918",
                        "displayName": "Steven Osborn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm kind of curious is there any reason this check could not be dropped completely.  I don't see any obvious reason why it needs to be there and it complicates things a bit for mod_rewrite users.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steve918",
                        "name": "steve918",
                        "displayName": "Steven Osborn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-01-27T14:02:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-01-27T14:02:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18633",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steve918",
                        "name": "steve918",
                        "displayName": "Steven Osborn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Heres an option:\n\nIn JanRain's implementation you actually pass  the return_to URL to the complete() function.\n\n$response = $this->consumer->complete($return_to);\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steve918",
                        "name": "steve918",
                        "displayName": "Steven Osborn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-01-28T14:25:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-01-28T14:25:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19010",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, but I'm not able to reproduce the issue.\nThe demo MVC application \"demo\/Zend\/OpenId\/mvc_auth\" works fine.\nThe bug is probably already fixed some time ago (svn diff -r 6835:7023 library\/Zend\/OpenId.php).\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-12T11:35:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-12T11:35:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19013",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steve918",
                        "name": "steve918",
                        "displayName": "Steven Osborn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hmm... I wasn't working out of SVN.  I believe I downloaded a nightly, but perhaps not.  I'll check it out via svn and give it another go.  Sorry.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=steve918",
                        "name": "steve918",
                        "displayName": "Steven Osborn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-12T12:39:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-12T12:39:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19269",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamschlag",
                        "name": "adamschlag",
                        "displayName": "Adam Schlag",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Dmity,\n\nThe issue is that on a CGI\/FastCGI setup (I'm using lighttpd myself) the variables that are being used to evaluate selfUrl don't give you what you need.\n\nFor example, when I load a URL such as http:\/\/localhost\/testmod\/testcontrol\/testaction and add a phpinfo() in there to check variables, this is what I see:\n\n$_SERVER['SCRIPT_URI'] is not set\n$_SERVER['HTTP_HOST'] is set to localhost\n$_SERVER['SERVER_PORT'] is set to 80\n$_SERVER['SERVER_NAME'] is set to localhost\n$_SERVER['SCRIPT_URL'] is not set\n$_SERVER['REDIRECT_URL'] is not set\n$_SERVER['PHP_SELF'] is set to \/index.php\n$_SERVER['SCRIPT_NAME'] is set to \/index.php\n$_SERVER['PATH_INFO'] has no value\n\nThe only variable that has the correct value for use in selfUrl (on my server) is $_SERVER['REQUEST_URI'].  But, I'm wondering, why you don't use functionality such as is found in Zend_Controller_Request_Http to do this work for you?  Why make this evaluation in two different ways?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamschlag",
                        "name": "adamschlag",
                        "displayName": "Adam Schlag",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-19T18:59:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-19T18:59:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19326",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dmitry",
                        "name": "dmitry",
                        "displayName": "Dmitry Stogov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Must be fixed now. Could you please verify it?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
